      "message": "[warning] Line 2243: Clearing an edition commit\u0027s `bodyOverwrite` no longer emits an update for the original message. Edition commits have `editions.empty()` and `CommitKey::EDIT`, so this branch erases their plugin data but intentionally skips adding anything to `signalMap`; clients render the original message with its edition list, so they can keep showing the stale overwrite until another refresh. When clearing a commit with `CommitKey::EDIT`, enqueue its original message.\n```suggestion\n                if (auto editIt \u003d msg-\u003ebody.find(CommitKey::EDIT);\n                    editIt !\u003d msg-\u003ebody.end() \u0026\u0026 !editIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n                    if (auto originalIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(editIt-\u003esecond);\n                        originalIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n                        signalMap[editIt-\u003esecond] \u003d *originalIt-\u003esecond;\n                    }\n                } else {\n                    signalMap[id] \u003d *msg;\n                }\n```",
